2026-04-16 12:20:27 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Load module main lamp', 'Load module indicator lamp', 'Load module series diode', 'Load module internal wiring between terminals, diode, and lamps'] hypothesis_explanation='When the load module (with its two cables) is connected directly across the known‑good power supply, with correct polarity and the supply LED lit, neither the main lamp nor the internal parallel indicator lamp turns on. This rules out any fault in the upstream control chain as a cause of the observed symptoms. Because both lamps are in parallel after a single series diode and share the same two terminals, the only way for both to remain dark under this direct‑connection test is that the load module itself is faulty: either the series diode is open, internal wiring between the terminals, diode, and lamps is open/miswired, or both lamps are open. Consequently, the root cause must reside within the load module and its internal components/wiring rather than in the power supply or control modules.'
