Instruction: With the load module still known-good, disconnect all other modules. Using a voltmeter, measure the voltage between the two power-supply output terminals (the two external cables) with the battery inserted and the supply LED on. Record the magnitude and which terminal is positive. Then, without changing the meter leads, reconnect the load module directly and confirm that the same terminal that was positive is connected to the 12V input of the load module (i.e., check for any polarity reversal or wrong cable pairing between power supply and load).
