description: Disconnect the load module (with its two attached cables) from the rest of the chain and connect it directly across the power supply output (respecting polarity) with the battery inserted and power LED on, then observe whether the main lamp or the internal lamp indicator turn on., outcome='The main load lamp is not lit when connected directly across the power supply output.  \nThe internal indicator lamp, which is in parallel with the main load, is also not lit.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('open_peephole', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Power supply output polarity and voltage,
description: With the load module still known-good, disconnect all other modules. Using a voltmeter, measure the voltage between the two power-supply output terminals (the two external cables) with the battery inserted and the supply LED on. Record the magnitude and which terminal is positive. Then, without changing the meter leads, reconnect the load module directly and confirm that the same terminal that was positive is connected to the 12V input of the load module (i.e., check for any polarity reversal or wrong cable pairing between power supply and load)., outcome='Power supply is providing approximately 12.0 V on PSU Output Cable (+) with PSU Output Cable (−) at 0 V. Load Input Cables (+) and (−) both read 0 V, indicating no supply voltage is presently reaching the load input.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Inter‑module cable chain between power supply and load (via control modules),
description: With battery inserted and PSU LED on, leave all cables plugged as in normal operation and use a voltmeter to probe each module’s two external terminals in sequence from the power supply towards the load. For each module, identify which terminal pair actually carries 12 V and continuity to the next module, and verify that one conductor of each outgoing pair is the same 12 V line and the other is the same 0 V line. Note at which point in the chain the 12 V (or 0 V) ceases to appear as expected, which would indicate a cable mis‑connection between specific modules., outcome='PSU Output Cable (+) is at 11.9893 V and PSU Output Cable (−) is at 0 V, and this same 12 V/0 V pairing propagates correctly through Control modules 1 and 2 and up to Control Input Cable (+/−) 3. From Control Output Cable (+/−) 3 onward (including all subsequent control outputs and the load cables), both conductors measure 0 V, indicating that the expected 12 V line ceases at Control Output Cable (+) 3. No POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED: at every measured point, the (+) cables carry ~12 V and the (−) cables carry 0 V where voltage is present.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=720.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
